In our cluster we are having 45 nodes with 2x8 core Intel processors each. Among that 3 nodes having 2 Intel MIC cards each, and 8 nodes having 2 NVIDIA GPU cards each. I am using torque 5.0.1 with torques FIFO scheduler. The 45 nodes are partitioned in to 4 queue, One of that will schedule the jobs only on the MIC nodes. Another will only schedule to GPU nodes. For GPU nodes queue is doing fine. For the MIC queue, When I submit a job with nodes=1:mics=1, its allotted to first node, and its first MIC card,  and if I submit another job with same spec, it allotted to the same first nodes next MIC. Up to this OK. Now if I submit a job on the queue  with same nodes=1:mics=1, instead of node2 of the mic nodes getting allotted, its being in queue. Same type of behavior for the spec nodes=1:mics=2. If I request nodes=1:ppn=8:mics=1 or nodes=1:ppn=16:mics=2, in this scenario the next node is getting allotted. But Once after the job ends on the allotted nodes, The scheduler is not allotting further jobs to these nodes. After restarting the server its allotting back.
Same type of behaviors in older version 4.2.8 and 4.2.9.

From this symptoms I cam to understand that, server is not accounting the used MICs and free MICs properly.

So I patched the node_manager.c file with the gpu code help for the version 5.0.1
After applying the patch, it scheduling properly as required

